# DTS AppPack Protocol (能力包协议规则)

Scope: all AppPack development under `/opt/prod/dts/rdc`

## Pack Manifest Standard

Every AppPack must contain a `pack-manifest.yaml` at root with the following structure:

```yaml
name: <pack-name>          # unique identifier
version: <semver>           # semantic versioning
vendor: <vendor-name>       # publisher
requires:
  dts-core: ">=x.y.z"      # minimum platform version

capabilities:
  ontology:                 # schema definitions → dts-ontology-store
  skills:                   # AI skills (gRPC endpoints) → dts-agent
  connectors:               # data source adapters → dts-data-connector
  frontend:                 # UI modules per webapp (cortex/pilot) → webapp loaders
  workflows:                # approval flow templates → dts-workflow
  persona:                  # industry persona (prompt + preferred skills + scheduled tasks) → dts-agent
  metrics:                  # metric definitions → dts-ontology-store
  quality_rules:            # data quality rules → dts-data-quality
  actions:                  # business actions with risk levels → dts-agent
  evaluations:              # evaluation datasets → dts-ai-eval
```

## Pack Lifecycle (managed by dts-operator)

1. Install: dts-operator pulls image → deploys Pod → reads manifest → registers all capabilities to respective services → status: Running.
2. Upgrade: dts-operator performs rolling update → re-registers capabilities → validates health.
3. Uninstall: check dependencies → deregister all capabilities → remove Pod → optionally retain data.

## Pack Security Rules

- All Pack API calls MUST go through dts-gateway. No direct service access.
- Pack Skills are subject to the same user permission checks as platform Skills.
- Pack Actions with risk_level: high automatically trigger HITL approval via dts-workflow.
- All Pack operations are recorded in dts-audit-log. No exemptions.
- Pack cannot register system-level permissions or modify platform RBAC rules.
- Pack data ingestion goes through dts-data-connector; raw database access is forbidden.

## Pack Development Guidelines

- Control plane: implement gRPC interfaces defined in platform proto files.
- Data plane: publish to designated Kafka topics (optional, for data-heavy Packs).
- Frontend: export ES modules loadable by webapp Pack loaders.
- Evaluation: provide at minimum 50 test cases in evaluations dataset.
- Persona: must include system_prompt and at least one preferred_skill.
